{"questionId":"19884473","questionHtml":"<p>Find the number of guesses required to decode a password that has an entropy of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn></math> bits. Write your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mi>k</mi></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>10</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> in given equation or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>G</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>301</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mi>G</mi></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>G</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>301</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>28</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>G</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>67916</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68</mn></math>, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup></math>. Award <em><strong>M1A1A0</strong></em> for a correct final answer not written in scientific notation or written incorrectly in scientific notation (e.g., <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>268</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>26</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>7</mn></msup></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>68</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mn>08</mn></math>).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19884473","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.8c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the number of guesses required to decode a password that has an entropy of 28 bits. Write your answer in the form a×10k, where 1≤a<10, k∈ℤ.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.1—Using standard form","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.5—Intro to logs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}